Simulation_Type.description: Type of disease being simulated. IDM-supported values include GENERIC_SIM, VECTOR_SIM, MALARIA_SIM, TBHIV_SIM, STI_SIM, HIV_SIM, ENVIRONMENTAL_SIM, and TYPHOID_SIM. To query the values supported for your specific build, use the --version option.

Simulation_Duration.description: Elapsed time noted in days from the start to the end of a simulation.

Simulation_Timestep.description: Value indicating simulation time step in days.

Start_Time.description: Time noted in days when the simulation begins. This time influences the point in the temporal input data, such as where in the climate input EMOD starts running the simulation. Note: The Start_Day of campaign events is in absolute time. So, time relative to the beginning of the simulation depends on this parameter.

Config_Name.description: The optional, user-supplied title naming a configuration.

Enable_Demographics_Builtin.description: Controls whether or not built-in demographics for default geography will be used. Note that the built-in demographics feature does not represent a real geographical location and is mostly used for testing.

Default_Geography_Initial_Node_Populatio.description: When using the built-in demographics for default geography, the initial number of individuals in each node.

Default_Geography_Torus_Size.description: When using the built-in demographics for default geography, the square root of the number of nodes in the simulation. For migration, the nodes are assumed to be a torus.

Node_Grid_Size.description: Spatial resolution indicating the node grid size for a simulation in degrees.

Migration_Model.description: Model to use for migration.  Note: VARIABLE_RATE_MIGRATION and LEVY FLIGHTS are currently not supported.

Enable_Interventions.description: Controls whether or not campaign interventions will be used in the simulation.

Enable_Heterogeneous_Intranode_Transmiss.description: Controls whether or not individuals experience heterogeneous disease transmission within a node.

Species.description: Name of the species of vectors.  Must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params>

Allele_Combinations.description: The combination of alleles that vectors must have in order to be resistant.  These alleles must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params.Genes.Alleles> for the associated species.

Larval_Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the larval killing effectivity of an intervention

Repelling_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the repelling effectivity of an intervention

Blocking_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the blocking effectivity of an intervention

Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the killing effectivity of an intervention

Resistances.description: An array of resistance modifier objects that define how to modify the efficacy of the insecticide for particular vector genomes.

Insecticides.description: An Array of insecticides and their resistance modifiers

Simulation_Type.description: Type of disease being simulated. IDM-supported values include GENERIC_SIM, VECTOR_SIM, MALARIA_SIM, TBHIV_SIM, STI_SIM, HIV_SIM, ENVIRONMENTAL_SIM, and TYPHOID_SIM. To query the values supported for your specific build, use the --version option.

Enable_Interventions.description: Controls whether or not campaign interventions will be used in the simulation.

Enable_Heterogeneous_Intranode_Transmiss.description: Controls whether or not individuals experience heterogeneous disease transmission within a node.

Egg_Hatch_Delay_Distribution.description: The distribution of the delay from oviposition to egg hatching.

Egg_Saturation_At_Oviposition.description: If laying all eggs from ovipositing females would overflow the larval habitat capacity on a given day, the means by which the viable eggs become saturated.

Larval_Density_Dependence.description: The funtional form of mortality and growth delay for mosquito larvae based on population density.

Egg_Hatch_Density_Dependence.description: The effect of larval density on egg hatching rate.

Vector_Larval_Rainfall_Mortality.description: Type of vector larval mortality function due to rainfall.

Larval_Rainfall_Mortality_Threshold.description: The threshold value on daily rainfall in millimeters, above which larval mortality is applied.

Enable_Temperature_Dependent_Egg_Hatchin.description: Controls whether or not temperature has an effect on egg hatching, defined by Egg_Arrhenius1 and Egg_Arrhenius2.

Egg_Arrhenius1.description: The temperature-independent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for egg hatching rate.

Egg_Arrhenius2.description: The temperature-dependent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for egg hatching rate.

Enable_Egg_Mortality.description: Controls whether or not to include a daily mortality rate on the egg population, which is independent of climatic factors.

Enable_Drought_Egg_Hatch_Delay.description: Controls whether or not eggs hatch at delayed rates, set by Drought_Egg_Hatch_Delay, when the habitat dries up completely.

Drought_Egg_Hatch_Delay.description: Proportion of regular egg hatching that still occurs when habitat dries up.

Larval_Density_Mortality_Scalar.description: A scale factor in the formula determining the larval-age-dependent mortality.

Larval_Density_Mortality_Offset.description: An offset factor in the formula determining the larval-age-dependent mortality.

Enable_Vector_Species_Report.description: A value of one will cause the VectorSpeciesReport.json file to be created.

Enable_Vector_Aging.description: Controls whether or not vectors undergo senescence as they age.

Mean_Egg_Hatch_Delay.description: The mean delay in egg hatch time, in days, from the time of oviposition.

Wolbachia_Mortality_Modification.description: The change in vector mortality due to a Wolbachia infection.

Wolbachia_Infection_Modification.description: The change in vector susceptibility to infection due to a Wolbachia infection.

Human_Feeding_Mortality.description: The fraction of mosquitoes, for all species, that die while feeding on a human.

Temporary_Habitat_Decay_Factor.description: Factor to convert raw evaporation rate (ignoring boundary layer effects) to the daily rate of larval habitat loss for temporary habitats (Habitats set to TEMPORARY_RAINFALL). Units are (larval carrying capacity per day) / (kg per square meter per second).

Semipermanent_Habitat_Decay_Rate.description: Daily rate of larval habitat loss for semi-permanent habitats with Habitats parameter value of WATER_VEGETATION or BRACKISH_SWAMP.

Rainfall_In_mm_To_Fill_Swamp.description: Millimeters of rain to fill larval habitat to capacity. Only used for vector species with Habitats set to BRACKISH_SWAMP.

x_Temporary_Larval_Habitat.description: Scale factor for the habitat size for all mosquito populations.

Name.description: Name of this species of vectors

Capacity_Distribution_Number_Of_Years.description: The total length of time in years for the scaling.  If the simulation goes longer than this time, the pattern will repeat.  Ideally, this value times 365 is the last value in 'Capacity_Distribution_Over_Time'.

Values.description: An array of values to match the defined Times.

Capacity_Distribution_Over_Time.description: This allows one to scale the larval capacity over time.  The Times and Values arrays must be the same length where Times is in days and Values are a scale factor per degrees squared.  The value is multiplied times the max capacity and 'Node_Grid_Size' squared/4. Ideally, you want the last value  to equal the first value if they are one day apart.  A point will be added if not.

Habitat_Type.description: The type of habitat that this species of vectors use for eggs.  Each species can have at most one of each type.  You cannot use ALL_HABITATS.

Habitats.description: A measure of the habitat type and scale factors used to estimate larval population.  Use each element in the array to specify a habitat type and max larval capacity. LINEAR_SPLINE has a more detailed scaling configuration.  See the documentation for more information.

Vector_Sugar_Feeding_Frequency.description: The frequency of sugar feeding by a female mosquito. Used in used in conjunction with the SugarTrap and OvipositionTrap interventions. Vector_Sampling_Type must be set to TRACK_ALL_VECTORS or SAMPLE_IND_VECTORS.

Aquatic_Arrhenius_1.description: The temperature-independent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for development rate as vectors progress from egg-hatching to emergence.

Aquatic_Arrhenius_2.description: The temperature-dependent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for development rate as vectors progress from egg-hatching to emergence.

Infected_Arrhenius_1.description: The temperature-independent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for sporogony as vectors progress from infected status to infectious.

Infected_Arrhenius_2.description: The temperature-dependent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for sporogony as vectors progress from infected status to infectious.

Temperature_Dependent_Feeding_Cycle.description: Effect of temperature on the duration between blood feeds.

Cycle_Arrhenius_1.description: The temperature-independent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for feeding cycle rate.

Cycle_Arrhenius_2.description: The temperature-dependent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for feeding cycle rate.

Cycle_Arrhenius_Reduction_Factor.description: The scale factor applied to cycle duration (from oviposition to oviposition) to reduce the duration when primary follicles are at stage II rather than I in the case of newly emerged females.

Immature_Duration.description: The number of days for larvae to develop into adult mosquitoes. The value is used to calculate mosquito development rate, which equals 1 / (value of this parameter). Note that development from immature individual to adult is not dependent on temperature.

Days_Between_Feeds.description: Factor (in days) used to calculate the daily rate, 1 / (value of this parameter), at which female mosquitoes attempt to feed.  The Days_Between_Feeds parameter represents a 3-day feeding cycle at normal tropical temperatures (30 C) 4 days at 24 C, and an increase in the fraction of 2-day cycles from 30 C to 48 C.

Anthropophily.description: Propensity of the mosquito to feed on humans instead of animals, measured as a fraction of blood meals from human hosts.

Egg_Batch_Size.description: Size of egg batch laid by one female mosquito that has fed successfully.

Infected_Egg_Batch_Factor.description: The dimensionless factor used to modify mosquito egg batch size  in order to account for reduced fertility effects arising due to infection (e.g. when females undergo sporogony).

Aquatic_Mortality_Rate.description: The base aquatic mortality per day for the species before adjusting for effects of overpopulation and drying out of aquatic habitat.

Adult_Life_Expectancy.description: Number of days an average female mosquito survives. The daily female mortality rate is 1 / (value of this parameter).

Male_Life_Expectancy.description: Number of days an average male mosquito survives. The daily male mortality rate is 1 / (value of this parameter).

Transmission_Rate.description: Probability that the bite of an infected mosquito establishes a new infection in an immunologically naive and uninfected individual, or the modifier of the probability of success for an individual with pre-erythrocytic immunity.

Acquire_Modifier.description: Modifier of the probability of successful infection of a mosquito by an infected individual, given the individual's infectiousness.

Infectious_Human_Feed_Mortality_Factor.description: The (dimensionless) factor used to modify the death rate of mosquitoes when feeding on humans, to account for the higher mortality rate infected mosquitoes experience during human feeds versus uninfected mosquitoes.

Indoor_Feeding_Fraction.description: The fraction (dimensionless) of feeds in which mosquitoes feed on humans indoors; the fraction of feeds on humans that occur outdoors equals 1 - (value of this parameter).

Is_Gender_Gene.description: True implies that the alleles of this gene are for gender.  If defining the gender gene, X & Y must be defined.  One can have 4 alleles of a particular gender type.

Name.description: The name of an allele at this locus.  It must be unique for a given species of vector.

Initial_Allele_Frequency.description: This is frequency of the allele at this locus in the population at initialization.

Is_Y_Chromosome.description: True implies that this allele represents the Y chromosome.  This can only be used when 'Is_Gender_Allele' is also true.

Alleles.description: This is an array of allele name-initial allele frequency pairs.  The initial frequencies of the alleles must add to one.  All possible allele of a gene must be defined here.  Allele names must be unique across all genes.  A gene can have a max of 8 alleles.

Mutate_From.description: If the allele in the gamete that could mutate.

Mutate_To.description: The allele that this locus will change to during gamete generation.

Probability_Of_Mutation.description: The probability that the allele will mutate from one allele to the other during the creation of the gametes.

Mutations.description: (Germline Mutation) This is an array of elements that define allele mutations that occur during the creation of the gametes. An allele cannot mutate into itself.

Genes.description: This is an array of Gene elements.  Each element defines all the possible allele for the gene and possible allele mutations.  Every vector will have two of the alleles of every gene.  There will be a max of 10 genes.  By default, one of the 10 genes is the gender 'gene' that has two alleles - X and Y.  This allows the user to use the X & Y alleles in Gene_To_Trait_Modifiers.

Allele_Combinations.description: This defines a possible subset of allele pairs that a vector could have.  Each pair are alleles from one gene.  If the vector has this subset, then the associated traits will be adjusted.  Order does not matter.  '*' is allowed when only the occurrence of one allele is important.

Trait.description: The trait to be modified of vectors with the given allele combination.

Modifier.description: The multiplier to use to modify the given trait for vectors with the given allele combination.

Trait_Modifiers.description: This is an array of trait-modifier pairs.  Vectors with the associated allele combination will have this set of traits modified.

Gene_To_Trait_Modifiers.description: This object defines that if a vector has a particular set of allele pairs, then some of their traits will be modified.  In most cases, this will consist of a single pair of allele associated with impact of one trait.  We provide support for the many-to-many case for when things aren't simple.

Driver_Type.description: This indicates the type of driver.  CLASSIC-The driver can only drive if the one gamete has the driving allele and the other has a specific allele to be replaced; INTEGRAL_AUTONOMOUS-At least one of the gametes must have the driver.  Alleles can still be driven if the driving allele is in both gametes or even if the driving allele cannot replace the allele in the other gamete.

Driving_Allele.description: This is the allele that is known as the driver.

Allele_To_Copy.description: The main allele to be copied.

Allele_To_Replace.description: The allele that must exist and will be replaced by the copy.

Copy_To_Allele.description: The name of the allele to be copied.  It must be an allele of the same gene as the 'Allele_To_Copy' and 'Allele_To_Repleace'.

Likelihood.description: The likelihood that the copy process will produce this allele.  If you give the 'Allele_To_Replace', you are defining the likelihood the copy fails.  If you give the 'Allele_To_Copy', you are specifying the likelihood of success.  Definitions for other alleles define possible mutations.

Copy_To_Likelihood.description: This is a dictionary of allele-to-likelihood.  If the other gamete has the 'Allele_To_Replace', this is the likelihood that it will result in one of the specified values.  Notice that you can specify the 'Allele_To_Copy' to indicate the probability that the copy failed or other alleles to account for mutation in the copy process.

Alleles_Driven.description: If the drive can be activated, then these elements define the probabilities of how alleles are copied.

Driving_Allele_Params.description: If the drive is X_SHRED or Y_SHRED and it can be activiated, then these parameters define how the driver is copied.

Allele_Required.description: The genome must have this gender allele in order for shredding to occur. If the driver is X_SHRED, then the allele must be designated as a Y chromosome. If the driver is Y_SHRED, then the allele must NOT be designated as a Y chromosome.

Allele_To_Shred.description: The genome must have this gender allele in order for shredding to occur. If the driver is X_SHRED, then the allele must NOT be designated as a Y chromosome. If the driver is Y_SHRED, then the allele must be designated as a Y chromosome.

Allele_To_Shred_To.description: This is a gender allele that the 'shredding' will change the Allele_To_Shred into. It can be a temporary allele that never exists in the output or could be something that appears due to resistance/failures.

Allele_Shredding_Fraction.description: This is the fraction of the Alleles_To_Shred that will be converted to Allele_To_Shred_To.  If this value is less than one, then some of the Allele_To_Shred will remain and be part of the gametes.

Allele_To_Shred_To_Surviving_Fraction.description: A trait modifier will automatically generated for [ Allele_To_Shred_To, * ], the trait ADJUST_FERTILE_EGGS, and this value as its modifier. A value of 0 implies perfect shredding such that no Allele_To_Shred_To survive in the eggs. A value of 1 means all of the 'shredded' alleles survive.

Shredding_Alleles.description: If the drive is X_SHRED or Y_SHRED and it can be activated, then these parameters define how gender alleles are shredded.

Drivers.description: This is an array of Driver elements.  They change the likelihood that other alleles will be propagated from one parent's gamete to the other parent's gamete when the cells merge.

Vector_Species_Params.description: A list of JSON object where each object contains the parameters for a specific species of vectors.

Species.description: Name of the species of vectors.  Must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params>

Allele_Combinations.description: The combination of alleles that vectors must have in order to be resistant.  These alleles must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params.Genes.Alleles> for the associated species.

Larval_Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the larval killing effectivity of an intervention

Repelling_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the repelling effectivity of an intervention

Blocking_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the blocking effectivity of an intervention

Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the killing effectivity of an intervention

Resistances.description: An array of resistance modifier objects that define how to modify the efficacy of the insecticide for particular vector genomes.

Insecticides.description: An Array of insecticides and their resistance modifiers

Modifier.description: The multiplier to use to modify the given trait for vectors with the given allele combination.

Trait_Modifiers.description: This is an array of trait-modifier pairs.  Vectors with the associated allele combination will have this set of traits modified.

Gene_To_Trait_Modifiers.description: This object defines that if a vector has a particular set of allele pairs, then some of their traits will be modified.  In most cases, this will consist of a single pair of allele associated with impact of one trait.  We provide support for the many-to-many case for when things aren't simple.

Driver_Type.description: This indicates the type of driver.  CLASSIC-The driver can only drive if the one gamete has the driving allele and the other has a specific allele to be replaced; INTEGRAL_AUTONOMOUS-At least one of the gametes must have the driver.  Alleles can still be driven if the driving allele is in both gametes or even if the driving allele cannot replace the allele in the other gamete.

Driving_Allele.description: This is the allele that is known as the driver.

Allele_To_Copy.description: The main allele to be copied.

Allele_To_Replace.description: The allele that must exist and will be replaced by the copy.

Copy_To_Allele.description: The name of the allele to be copied.  It must be an allele of the same gene as the 'Allele_To_Copy' and 'Allele_To_Repleace'.

Likelihood.description: The likelihood that the copy process will produce this allele.  If you give the 'Allele_To_Replace', you are defining the likelihood the copy fails.  If you give the 'Allele_To_Copy', you are specifying the likelihood of success.  Definitions for other alleles define possible mutations.

Copy_To_Likelihood.description: This is a dictionary of allele-to-likelihood.  If the other gamete has the 'Allele_To_Replace', this is the likelihood that it will result in one of the specified values.  Notice that you can specify the 'Allele_To_Copy' to indicate the probability that the copy failed or other alleles to account for mutation in the copy process.

Alleles_Driven.description: If the drive can be activated, then these elements define the probabilities of how alleles are copied.

Driving_Allele_Params.description: If the drive is X_SHRED or Y_SHRED and it can be activiated, then these parameters define how the driver is copied.

Allele_Required.description: The genome must have this gender allele in order for shredding to occur. If the driver is X_SHRED, then the allele must be designated as a Y chromosome. If the driver is Y_SHRED, then the allele must NOT be designated as a Y chromosome.

Allele_To_Shred.description: The genome must have this gender allele in order for shredding to occur. If the driver is X_SHRED, then the allele must NOT be designated as a Y chromosome. If the driver is Y_SHRED, then the allele must be designated as a Y chromosome.

Allele_To_Shred_To.description: This is a gender allele that the 'shredding' will change the Allele_To_Shred into. It can be a temporary allele that never exists in the output or could be something that appears due to resistance/failures.

Allele_Shredding_Fraction.description: This is the fraction of the Alleles_To_Shred that will be converted to Allele_To_Shred_To.  If this value is less than one, then some of the Allele_To_Shred will remain and be part of the gametes.

Allele_To_Shred_To_Surviving_Fraction.description: A trait modifier will automatically generated for [ Allele_To_Shred_To, * ], the trait ADJUST_FERTILE_EGGS, and this value as its modifier. A value of 0 implies perfect shredding such that no Allele_To_Shred_To survive in the eggs. A value of 1 means all of the 'shredded' alleles survive.

Shredding_Alleles.description: If the drive is X_SHRED or Y_SHRED and it can be activated, then these parameters define how gender alleles are shredded.

Drivers.description: This is an array of Driver elements.  They change the likelihood that other alleles will be propagated from one parent's gamete to the other parent's gamete when the cells merge.

Vector_Species_Params.description: A list of JSON object where each object contains the parameters for a specific species of vectors.

Species.description: Name of the species of vectors.  Must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params>

Allele_Combinations.description: The combination of alleles that vectors must have in order to be resistant.  These alleles must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params.Genes.Alleles> for the associated species.

Larval_Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the larval killing effectivity of an intervention

Repelling_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the repelling effectivity of an intervention

Blocking_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the blocking effectivity of an intervention

Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the killing effectivity of an intervention

Possible values are: POLIO_EVOCLOCK_NONE, POLIO_EVOCLOCK_LINEAR, POLIO_EVOCLOCK_IMMUNITY, POLIO_EVOCLOCK_REVERSION_AND_IMMUNITY, POLIO_EVOCLOCK_REVERSION

Possible values are: POLIO_VDPV_NONVIRULENT, POLIO_VDPV_PARALYSIS, POLIO_VDPV_PARALYSIS_AND_LOG_INFECTIVITY, POLIO_VDPV_LOG_PARALYSIS_AND_LOG_INFECTIVITY

Max_Rand_Standard_Deviations.description: Limit to extents of a random normal as number of standard deviations.

Viral_Interference_WPV1.description: Probability that a WPV1 infection in an individual will block infection by any other poliovirus type.

Viral_Interference_WPV2.description: Probability that a WPV2 infection in an individual will block infection by any other poliovirus type.

Viral_Interference_WPV3.description: Probability that a WPV3 infection in an individual will block infection by any other poliovirus type.

Viral_Interference_Sabin1.description: Probability that a Sabin1 infection in an individual will block superinfection by any other poliovirus type.

Viral_Interference_Sabin2.description: Probability that a Sabin2 infection in an individual will block superinfection by any other poliovirus type.

Viral_Interference_Sabin3.description: Probability that a Sabin3 infection in an individual will block superinfection by any other poliovirus type.

Vaccine_Take_Scaling_Sabin1.description: A multiplier to represent vaccine take of live Sabin virus for type 1.

Vaccine_Take_Scaling_Sabin2.description: A multiplier to represent vaccine take of live Sabin virus for type 2.

Vaccine_Take_Scaling_Sabin3.description: A multiplier to represent vaccine take of live Sabin virus for type 3.

Mucosal_Immunogenicity_IPV_OPVExposed.description: The mucosal immunogenicity of IPV relative to OPV on OPV-exposed individuals.

Neutralization_Time_Tau.description: Virus neutralization time constant in days.

Paralysis_Base_Rate_WPV2.description: Probability of paralysis from a WPV2 poliovirus infection in a fully susceptible individual.

Paralysis_Base_Rate_WPV3.description: Probability of paralysis from a WPV3 poliovirus infection in a fully susceptible individual.

Incubation_Disease_Sigma.description: Incubation period to disease, sigma parameter, in polio these are interpreted as lognormal

TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate.description: The daily rate at which treatment with an anti-TB drug causes inactivation in an individual with drug-sensitive TB.

TB_Drug_Cure_Rate.description: The daily probability of TB cure in an individual with drug-sensitive TB under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Resistance_Rate.description: The daily probability that an individual with drug-sensitive TB will acquire MDR-TB under drug treatment. Only individuals who return to the latent state or fail can acquire MDR-TB.

TB_Drug_Relapse_Rate.description: The daily probability of TB inactivation and subsequent relapse in an individual with drug-sensitive TB under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Mortality_Rate.description: The daily rate at which treatment with an anti-TB drug causes death  in an individual with drug-sensitive TB.

TB_Drug_Primary_Decay_Time_Constant.description: The number of days before the efficacy of a specific anti-TB drug begins to decay.

TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate_HIV.description: The daily probability of active drug-sensitive TB infection becoming latent in an HIV+ person, not currently on ART, under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate_MDR.description: The daily probability of active MDR infection becoming latent in an HIV+ or HIV-  person under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Cure_Rate_HIV.description: The daily probability of active TB infection being cured in an HIV+ person under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Cure_Rate_MDR.description: The daily probability of active MDR infection being cured in an HIV+ or HIV- person under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Resistance_Rate_HIV.description: The daily probability that an (HIV+) individual with drug-sensitive TB will acquire MDR-TB under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Relapse_Rate_MDR.description: The daily probability that an active MDR-TB infection (in HIV+ or HIV-) will inactivate but subsequently relapse under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Relapse_Rate_HIV.description: The daily probability that a drug-sensitive active infection in an HIV+ individual not currently on ART will inactivate but subsequently relapse under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Mortality_Rate_MDR.description: The daily probability of death for individual with MDR active infection under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Mortality_Rate_HIV.description: The daily probability of death for HIV+ individual with drug sensitive active infection under drug treatment.

TB_Reduced_Transmit.description: Proportion reduction in TB transmission under drug treatment.

TB_Reduced_Acquire.description: Proportion reduction in acquisition of new TB infection under drug treatment.

Default_Geography_Torus_Size.description: When using the built-in demographics for default geography, the square root of the number of nodes in the simulation. For migration, the nodes are assumed to be a torus.

Node_Grid_Size.description: Spatial resolution indicating the node grid size for a simulation in degrees.

Migration_Model.description: Model to use for migration.  Note: VARIABLE_RATE_MIGRATION and LEVY FLIGHTS are currently not supported.

Enable_Interventions.description: Controls whether or not campaign interventions will be used in the simulation.

Enable_Heterogeneous_Intranode_Transmiss.description: Controls whether or not individuals experience heterogeneous disease transmission within a node.

Species.description: Name of the species of vectors.  Must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params>

Allele_Combinations.description: The combination of alleles that vectors must have in order to be resistant.  These alleles must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params.Genes.Alleles> for the associated species.

Larval_Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the larval killing effectivity of an intervention

Repelling_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the repelling effectivity of an intervention

Blocking_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the blocking effectivity of an intervention

Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the killing effectivity of an intervention

Resistances.description: An array of resistance modifier objects that define how to modify the efficacy of the insecticide for particular vector genomes.

Insecticides.description: An Array of insecticides and their resistance modifiers

Simulation_Type.description: Type of disease being simulated. IDM-supported values include GENERIC_SIM, VECTOR_SIM, MALARIA_SIM, TBHIV_SIM, STI_SIM, HIV_SIM, ENVIRONMENTAL_SIM, and TYPHOID_SIM. To query the values supported for your specific build, use the --version option.

Simulation_Duration.description: Elapsed time noted in days from the start to the end of a simulation.

Simulation_Timestep.description: Value indicating simulation time step in days.

Start_Time.description: Time noted in days when the simulation begins. This time influences the point in the temporal input data, such as where in the climate input EMOD starts running the simulation. Note: The Start_Day of campaign events is in absolute time. So, time relative to the beginning of the simulation depends on this parameter.

Config_Name.description: The optional, user-supplied title naming a configuration.

Default_Geography_Initial_Node_Populatio.description: When using the built-in demographics for default geography, the initial number of individuals in each node.

Default_Geography_Torus_Size.description: When using the built-in demographics for default geography, the square root of the number of nodes in the simulation. For migration, the nodes are assumed to be a torus.

Node_Grid_Size.description: Spatial resolution indicating the node grid size for a simulation in degrees.

Migration_Model.description: Model to use for migration.  Note: VARIABLE_RATE_MIGRATION and LEVY FLIGHTS are currently not supported.

Enable_Interventions.description: Controls whether or not campaign interventions will be used in the simulation.

Enable_Heterogeneous_Intranode_Transmiss.description: Controls whether or not individuals experience heterogeneous disease transmission within a node.

Egg_Hatch_Delay_Distribution.description: The distribution of the delay from oviposition to egg hatching.

Egg_Saturation_At_Oviposition.description: If laying all eggs from ovipositing females would overflow the larval habitat capacity on a given day, the means by which the viable eggs become saturated.

Larval_Density_Dependence.description: The funtional form of mortality and growth delay for mosquito larvae based on population density.

Egg_Hatch_Density_Dependence.description: The effect of larval density on egg hatching rate.

Vector_Larval_Rainfall_Mortality.description: Type of vector larval mortality function due to rainfall.

Larval_Rainfall_Mortality_Threshold.description: The threshold value on daily rainfall in millimeters, above which larval mortality is applied.

Enable_Temperature_Dependent_Egg_Hatchin.description: Controls whether or not temperature has an effect on egg hatching, defined by Egg_Arrhenius1 and Egg_Arrhenius2.

Egg_Arrhenius1.description: The temperature-independent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for egg hatching rate.

Egg_Arrhenius2.description: The temperature-dependent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for egg hatching rate.

Enable_Egg_Mortality.description: Controls whether or not to include a daily mortality rate on the egg population, which is independent of climatic factors.

Enable_Drought_Egg_Hatch_Delay.description: Controls whether or not eggs hatch at delayed rates, set by Drought_Egg_Hatch_Delay, when the habitat dries up completely.

Drought_Egg_Hatch_Delay.description: Proportion of regular egg hatching that still occurs when habitat dries up.

Larval_Density_Mortality_Scalar.description: A scale factor in the formula determining the larval-age-dependent mortality.

Larval_Density_Mortality_Offset.description: An offset factor in the formula determining the larval-age-dependent mortality.

Enable_Vector_Species_Report.description: A value of one will cause the VectorSpeciesReport.json file to be created.

Enable_Vector_Aging.description: Controls whether or not vectors undergo senescence as they age.

Mean_Egg_Hatch_Delay.description: The mean delay in egg hatch time, in days, from the time of oviposition.

Wolbachia_Mortality_Modification.description: The change in vector mortality due to a Wolbachia infection.

Wolbachia_Infection_Modification.description: The change in vector susceptibility to infection due to a Wolbachia infection.

Human_Feeding_Mortality.description: The fraction of mosquitoes, for all species, that die while feeding on a human.

Temporary_Habitat_Decay_Factor.description: Factor to convert raw evaporation rate (ignoring boundary layer effects) to the daily rate of larval habitat loss for temporary habitats (Habitats set to TEMPORARY_RAINFALL). Units are (larval carrying capacity per day) / (kg per square meter per second).

Semipermanent_Habitat_Decay_Rate.description: Daily rate of larval habitat loss for semi-permanent habitats with Habitats parameter value of WATER_VEGETATION or BRACKISH_SWAMP.

Rainfall_In_mm_To_Fill_Swamp.description: Millimeters of rain to fill larval habitat to capacity. Only used for vector species with Habitats set to BRACKISH_SWAMP.

x_Temporary_Larval_Habitat.description: Scale factor for the habitat size for all mosquito populations.

Name.description: Name of this species of vectors

Capacity_Distribution_Number_Of_Years.description: The total length of time in years for the scaling.  If the simulation goes longer than this time, the pattern will repeat.  Ideally, this value times 365 is the last value in 'Capacity_Distribution_Over_Time'.

Values.description: An array of values to match the defined Times.

Capacity_Distribution_Over_Time.description: This allows one to scale the larval capacity over time.  The Times and Values arrays must be the same length where Times is in days and Values are a scale factor per degrees squared.  The value is multiplied times the max capacity and 'Node_Grid_Size' squared/4. Ideally, you want the last value  to equal the first value if they are one day apart.  A point will be added if not.

Habitat_Type.description: The type of habitat that this species of vectors use for eggs.  Each species can have at most one of each type.  You cannot use ALL_HABITATS.

Habitats.description: A measure of the habitat type and scale factors used to estimate larval population.  Use each element in the array to specify a habitat type and max larval capacity. LINEAR_SPLINE has a more detailed scaling configuration.  See the documentation for more information.

Vector_Sugar_Feeding_Frequency.description: The frequency of sugar feeding by a female mosquito. Used in used in conjunction with the SugarTrap and OvipositionTrap interventions. Vector_Sampling_Type must be set to TRACK_ALL_VECTORS or SAMPLE_IND_VECTORS.

Aquatic_Arrhenius_1.description: The temperature-independent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for development rate as vectors progress from egg-hatching to emergence.

Aquatic_Arrhenius_2.description: The temperature-dependent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for development rate as vectors progress from egg-hatching to emergence.

Infected_Arrhenius_1.description: The temperature-independent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for sporogony as vectors progress from infected status to infectious.

Infected_Arrhenius_2.description: The temperature-dependent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for sporogony as vectors progress from infected status to infectious.

Temperature_Dependent_Feeding_Cycle.description: Effect of temperature on the duration between blood feeds.

Cycle_Arrhenius_1.description: The temperature-independent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for feeding cycle rate.

Cycle_Arrhenius_2.description: The temperature-dependent scale factor in the Arrhenius equation for feeding cycle rate.

Cycle_Arrhenius_Reduction_Factor.description: The scale factor applied to cycle duration (from oviposition to oviposition) to reduce the duration when primary follicles are at stage II rather than I in the case of newly emerged females.

Immature_Duration.description: The number of days for larvae to develop into adult mosquitoes. The value is used to calculate mosquito development rate, which equals 1 / (value of this parameter). Note that development from immature individual to adult is not dependent on temperature.

Days_Between_Feeds.description: Factor (in days) used to calculate the daily rate, 1 / (value of this parameter), at which female mosquitoes attempt to feed.  The Days_Between_Feeds parameter represents a 3-day feeding cycle at normal tropical temperatures (30 C) 4 days at 24 C, and an increase in the fraction of 2-day cycles from 30 C to 48 C.

Anthropophily.description: Propensity of the mosquito to feed on humans instead of animals, measured as a fraction of blood meals from human hosts.

Egg_Batch_Size.description: Size of egg batch laid by one female mosquito that has fed successfully.

Infected_Egg_Batch_Factor.description: The dimensionless factor used to modify mosquito egg batch size  in order to account for reduced fertility effects arising due to infection (e.g. when females undergo sporogony).

Aquatic_Mortality_Rate.description: The base aquatic mortality per day for the species before adjusting for effects of overpopulation and drying out of aquatic habitat.

Adult_Life_Expectancy.description: Number of days an average female mosquito survives. The daily female mortality rate is 1 / (value of this parameter).

Male_Life_Expectancy.description: Number of days an average male mosquito survives. The daily male mortality rate is 1 / (value of this parameter).

Transmission_Rate.description: Probability that the bite of an infected mosquito establishes a new infection in an immunologically naive and uninfected individual, or the modifier of the probability of success for an individual with pre-erythrocytic immunity.

Acquire_Modifier.description: Modifier of the probability of successful infection of a mosquito by an infected individual, given the individual's infectiousness.

Infectious_Human_Feed_Mortality_Factor.description: The (dimensionless) factor used to modify the death rate of mosquitoes when feeding on humans, to account for the higher mortality rate infected mosquitoes experience during human feeds versus uninfected mosquitoes.

Indoor_Feeding_Fraction.description: The fraction (dimensionless) of feeds in which mosquitoes feed on humans indoors; the fraction of feeds on humans that occur outdoors equals 1 - (value of this parameter).

Is_Gender_Gene.description: True implies that the alleles of this gene are for gender.  If defining the gender gene, X & Y must be defined.  One can have 4 alleles of a particular gender type.

Name.description: The name of an allele at this locus.  It must be unique for a given species of vector.

Initial_Allele_Frequency.description: This is frequency of the allele at this locus in the population at initialization.

Is_Y_Chromosome.description: True implies that this allele represents the Y chromosome.  This can only be used when 'Is_Gender_Allele' is also true.

Alleles.description: This is an array of allele name-initial allele frequency pairs.  The initial frequencies of the alleles must add to one.  All possible allele of a gene must be defined here.  Allele names must be unique across all genes.  A gene can have a max of 8 alleles.

Mutate_From.description: If the allele in the gamete that could mutate.

Mutate_To.description: The allele that this locus will change to during gamete generation.

Probability_Of_Mutation.description: The probability that the allele will mutate from one allele to the other during the creation of the gametes.

Mutations.description: (Germline Mutation) This is an array of elements that define allele mutations that occur during the creation of the gametes. An allele cannot mutate into itself.

Genes.description: This is an array of Gene elements.  Each element defines all the possible allele for the gene and possible allele mutations.  Every vector will have two of the alleles of every gene.  There will be a max of 10 genes.  By default, one of the 10 genes is the gender 'gene' that has two alleles - X and Y.  This allows the user to use the X & Y alleles in Gene_To_Trait_Modifiers.

Allele_Combinations.description: This defines a possible subset of allele pairs that a vector could have.  Each pair are alleles from one gene.  If the vector has this subset, then the associated traits will be adjusted.  Order does not matter.  '*' is allowed when only the occurrence of one allele is important.

Trait.description: The trait to be modified of vectors with the given allele combination.

Modifier.description: The multiplier to use to modify the given trait for vectors with the given allele combination.

Trait_Modifiers.description: This is an array of trait-modifier pairs.  Vectors with the associated allele combination will have this set of traits modified.

Gene_To_Trait_Modifiers.description: This object defines that if a vector has a particular set of allele pairs, then some of their traits will be modified.  In most cases, this will consist of a single pair of allele associated with impact of one trait.  We provide support for the many-to-many case for when things aren't simple.

Driver_Type.description: This indicates the type of driver.  CLASSIC-The driver can only drive if the one gamete has the driving allele and the other has a specific allele to be replaced; INTEGRAL_AUTONOMOUS-At least one of the gametes must have the driver.  Alleles can still be driven if the driving allele is in both gametes or even if the driving allele cannot replace the allele in the other gamete.

Driving_Allele.description: This is the allele that is known as the driver.

Allele_To_Copy.description: The main allele to be copied.

Allele_To_Replace.description: The allele that must exist and will be replaced by the copy.

Copy_To_Allele.description: The name of the allele to be copied.  It must be an allele of the same gene as the 'Allele_To_Copy' and 'Allele_To_Repleace'.

Likelihood.description: The likelihood that the copy process will produce this allele.  If you give the 'Allele_To_Replace', you are defining the likelihood the copy fails.  If you give the 'Allele_To_Copy', you are specifying the likelihood of success.  Definitions for other alleles define possible mutations.

Copy_To_Likelihood.description: This is a dictionary of allele-to-likelihood.  If the other gamete has the 'Allele_To_Replace', this is the likelihood that it will result in one of the specified values.  Notice that you can specify the 'Allele_To_Copy' to indicate the probability that the copy failed or other alleles to account for mutation in the copy process.

Alleles_Driven.description: If the drive can be activated, then these elements define the probabilities of how alleles are copied.

Driving_Allele_Params.description: If the drive is X_SHRED or Y_SHRED and it can be activiated, then these parameters define how the driver is copied.

Allele_Required.description: The genome must have this gender allele in order for shredding to occur. If the driver is X_SHRED, then the allele must be designated as a Y chromosome. If the driver is Y_SHRED, then the allele must NOT be designated as a Y chromosome.

Allele_To_Shred.description: The genome must have this gender allele in order for shredding to occur. If the driver is X_SHRED, then the allele must NOT be designated as a Y chromosome. If the driver is Y_SHRED, then the allele must be designated as a Y chromosome.

Allele_To_Shred_To.description: This is a gender allele that the 'shredding' will change the Allele_To_Shred into. It can be a temporary allele that never exists in the output or could be something that appears due to resistance/failures.

Allele_Shredding_Fraction.description: This is the fraction of the Alleles_To_Shred that will be converted to Allele_To_Shred_To.  If this value is less than one, then some of the Allele_To_Shred will remain and be part of the gametes.

Allele_To_Shred_To_Surviving_Fraction.description: A trait modifier will automatically generated for [ Allele_To_Shred_To, * ], the trait ADJUST_FERTILE_EGGS, and this value as its modifier. A value of 0 implies perfect shredding such that no Allele_To_Shred_To survive in the eggs. A value of 1 means all of the 'shredded' alleles survive.

Shredding_Alleles.description: If the drive is X_SHRED or Y_SHRED and it can be activated, then these parameters define how gender alleles are shredded.

Drivers.description: This is an array of Driver elements.  They change the likelihood that other alleles will be propagated from one parent's gamete to the other parent's gamete when the cells merge.

Vector_Species_Params.description: A list of JSON object where each object contains the parameters for a specific species of vectors.

Species.description: Name of the species of vectors.  Must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params>

Allele_Combinations.description: The combination of alleles that vectors must have in order to be resistant.  These alleles must be defined in <config.Vector_Species_Params.Genes.Alleles> for the associated species.

Larval_Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the larval killing effectivity of an intervention

Repelling_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the repelling effectivity of an intervention

Blocking_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the blocking effectivity of an intervention

Killing_Modifier.description: The value used to modify (multiply) the killing effectivity of an intervention

Insecticides.description: An Array of insecticides and their resistance modifiers
