Drug_PKPD_C50.description: The concentration at which drug killing rates are half of maximum.

Drug_Vd.description: The volume of drug distribution in a pharmacokinetic two compartment model. This value is the ratio of the volume of the second compartment to that of the first.

Drug_Decay_T1.description: The primary drug decay rate, in days.

Drug_Decay_T2.description: The secondary drug decay rate, in days.

Drug_Fulltreatment_Doses.description: The number of doses for a full treatment.

Drug_Dose_Interval.description: The interval between doses, in days.

Bodyweight_Exponent.description: Effect of body weight on maximum drug concentration in an individual patient.

Drug_Resistant_String.description: A series of nucleotide base letters (A, C, G, T) that represent the drug resistant values at locations in the genome.  There must be one character for each location defined in <config>.Parasite_Genetics.Drug_Resistant_Genome_Locations.

PKPD_C50_Modifier.description: If the parasite has this drug resistant string, this value will be multiplied times the 'Drug_PKPD_C50' value of the drug.  Genomes with multiple matching strings will be simply multiplied together.

Max_IRBC_Kill_Modifier.description: If the parasite has this drug resistant string, this value will be multiplied times the 'Max_Drug_IRBC_Kill' value of the drug.  Genomes with multiple matching strings will be simply multiplied together.

Upper_Age_In_Years.description: The age, in years, below which children are given a fraction of the adult drug dose, as defined in Fraction_Of_Adult_Dose.

Fraction_Of_Adult_Dose.description: The fraction of the adult drug dose given to children below the age defined in Upper_Age_In_Years.

Fractional_Dose_By_Upper_Age.description: The fraction of the adult drug dose given to children below the age defined in Upper_Age_In_Years.

Malaria_Drug_Params.description: This JSON structure contains the names of anti-malarial drugs and the parameters that define them.

PFA_Cum_Prob_Selection_Threshold.description: This parameter serves to minimize the extent to which relationships with unlikely age gaps are formed. These unlikely relationships could be generated due to lack of diversity in the PFA. Within the algorithm, males pick from amongst the available females by age bin, weighted by the conditional of the joint_probability matrix given the male age bin.  If the sum of the probabilities in the female age bins that are not empty is below this threshold, the male will wait till the next update. Setting this parameter to 0 disables the feature.

Post_Infection_Acquisition_Multiplier.description: Multiplicative reduction in probability of reacquiring the disease.

Post_Infection_Transmission_Multiplier.description: Multiplicative reduction in probability of transmitting infection after getting re-infected.

Post_Infection_Mortality_Multiplier.description: Multiplicative reduction in probability of dying from infection after getting re-infected.

Enable_Immune_Decay.description: Controls whether or not immunity decays after an infection clears.

Acquisition_Blocking_Immunity_Decay_Rate.description: The rate at which acquisition-blocking immunity decays after the initial period indicated by the base acquisition-blocking immunity offset.

Transmission_Blocking_Immunity_Decay_Rat.description: Rate at which transmission-blocking immunity decays after the base transmission-blocking immunity offset period. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Mortality_Blocking_Immunity_Decay_Rate.description: Rate at which mortality-blocking immunity decays after the mortality-blocking immunity offset period.

Acquisition_Blocking_Immunity_Duration_B.description: The number of days after infection until acquisition-blocking immunity begins to decay.

Transmission_Blocking_Immunity_Duration_.description: Number of days after infection until transmission-blocking immunity begins to decay. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Mortality_Blocking_Immunity_Duration_Bef.description: Number of days after infection until mortality-blocking immunity begins to decay.

Enable_Maternal_Protection.description: Controls whether or not mothers pass immunity on to their infants. Setting to 1 (true) enables maternal protection as defined by Maternal_Protection_Type.

Maternal_Protection_Type.description: The type of maternal protection afforded to infants.

Maternal_Linear_Slope.description: Slope parameter describing the rate of waning for maternal protection, must be positive. The per-day increase in susceptibility.

Maternal_Linear_SusZero.description: The initial level of maternal protection at age 0, given as susceptibility. A value of 0.0 implies total protection, a value of 1.0 implies no protection.

Maternal_Sigmoid_SteepFac.description: The steepness factor describing the rate of waning for maternal protection, must be positive. Small values imply rapid waning.

Maternal_Sigmoid_HalfMaxAge.description: The age in days that the level of maternal protection is half of its initial value.

Maternal_Sigmoid_SusInit.description: The initial level of maternal protection at age -INF, given as susceptibility. A value of 0.0 implies total protection, a value of 1.0 implies no protection.

Susceptibility_Type.description: Controls implementation of an individual's susceptibility.

Enable_Initial_Susceptibility_Distributi.description: Controls whether or not individuals in the population have immunity at the beginning of the simulation. If set to 0, individuals are not initialized with immunity but may acquire immunity. If set to 1, you must indicate the type of distribution to use for immunity in the configuration parameter Immunity_Initialization_Distribution_Type and the distribution values in the demographics file.

Susceptibility_Initialization_Distributi.description: The method for initializing the susceptibility distribution in the simulated population.

TB_Immune_Loss_Fraction.description: The fraction of individuals that lose immunity with time.

TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Child.description: Fraction of active cases in children (under age 15) that are smear-positive. The sum of TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Child and TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Child must be less than or equal to 1.

TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Adult.description: Fraction of active cases in adults (age 15 and over) that are smear-positive. The sum of TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Adult and TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Adult must be less than or equal to 1.

TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Child.description: Fraction of active cases in children (under age 15) that are extrapulmonary. The sum of this and TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Child must be less than or equal to 1.

TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Adult.description: Fraction of active cases in adults (age 15 or over) that are extrapulmonary. The sum of this and TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Adult must be less than or equal to 1.

TB_Fast_Progressor_Fraction_Type.description: enable fast progressor fraction by age or social determinants like poverty

TB_Fast_Progressor_Fraction_Child.description: Fraction of children (under age 15) that are fast progressors.

TB_Fast_Progressor_Fraction_Adult.description: Fraction of adults (age 15 or over) that are fast progressors.

TB_Latent_Cure_Rate.description: The mean rate at which individuals progress from a latently infected state to a cured (uninfected) state.

TB_Fast_Progressor_Rate.description: The mean rate at which individuals who are fast progressors progress from a latently infected state to an active presymptomatic state.

TB_Slow_Progressor_Rate.description: The mean rate at which individuals who are slow progressors progress from a latently infected state to an active presymptomatic state.

TB_Active_Cure_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active symptomatic individuals progress to a cured (uninfected) state.

TB_Inactivation_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active symptomatic (smear-positive, smear-negative, and extrapulmonary) individuals progress to an inactivated (latently infected) state.

TB_Active_Mortality_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active smear-positive individuals die from TB disease.

TB_Extrapulmonary_Mortality_Multiplier.description: Scale factor for TB_Active_Mortality_Rate to give the mortality rate of active extrapulmonary individuals.

TB_Smear_Negative_Mortality_Multiplier.description: For individuals with smear-negative TB, scale factor to increase the mortality rate set by TB_Active_Mortality_Rate.

TB_Active_Presymptomatic_Infectivity_Mul.description: Scale factor for Base_Infectivity to give the infectiousness of active presymptomatic individuals.

TB_Presymptomatic_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active presymptomatic individuals progress to an active symptomatic state.

TB_Presymptomatic_Cure_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active presymptomatic individuals progress to a cured (uninfected) state

TB_Smear_Negative_Infectivity_Multiplier.description: Scale factor for Base_Infectivity to give the infectiousness of active smear-negative individuals.

TB_Drug_Efficacy_Multiplier_MDR.description: Scale factor for drug efficacy parameters (TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate and TB_Drug_Cure_Rate) to give the efficacy of first-line drugs when given to individuals with MDR-TB.

TB_Drug_Efficacy_Multiplier_Failed.description: Scale factor for drug efficacy parameters (TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate and TB_Drug_Cure_Rate) to give the efficacy of first-line drugs when given to individuals who have failed treatment.

TB_Drug_Efficacy_Multiplier_Relapsed.description: Scale factor for drug efficacy parameters (TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate and TB_Drug_Cure_Rate) to give the efficacy of first-line drugs when given to individuals who have relapsed after treatment.

TB_MDR_Fitness_Multiplier.description: Scale factor for Base_Infectivity to give the infectiousness of MDR-TB strains.

TB_Relapsed_to_Active_Rate.description: The mean rate at which relapsed individuals progress to an active symptomatic state.

TB_Active_Period_Distribution.description: Distribution for duration of active disease. For both possible values, the mean is defined by total rate, which is the sum of TB_Inactivation_Rate and TB_Active_Mortality_Rate corrected for smear status. For GAUSSIAN_DURATION, an additional parameter TB_Active_Period_Std_Dev is used to provide a value for standard deviation.

TB_Active_Period_Gaussian_Std_Dev.description: When TB_Active_Period_Distribution is set to GAUSSIAN_DURATION, the value for standard deviation.

TB_CD4_Activation_Vector.description: The increased risk per time step of TB activation by CD4 strata defined in CD4_Strata_Activation.

CD4_Strata_Activation.description: An array of CD4 count thresholds by which to stratify the population.

Enable_Coinfection.description: Controls whether or not coinfection incidence is enabled.

CoInfection_Mortality_Rate_On_ART.description: The daily rate of death in excess to TB when coinfected with HIV on ART.

CoInfection_Mortality_Rate_Off_ART.description: The daily rate of death in excess to TB when coinfected with HIV off ART.

TB_CD4_Infectiousness.description: Relative multiplicative increase in TB Infectiousness due to HIV positivity/CD4 decline.

TB_CD4_Susceptibility.description: Relative increase in TB susceptibility due to HIV/CD4 decline.

TB_CD4_Primary_Progression.description: The proportion (multiplier) increase in primary progression with by CD4.

TB_CD4_Strata_Infectiousness_Susceptibil.description: The CD4 strata defining increases and decreases in TB infectiousness and susceptibility.

ART_Reactivation_Factor.description: Factor for ART reducing reactivation in HIV+.

TB_Enable_Exogenous.description: Controls whether or not exogenous reinfection of latent TB can occur.

Enable_Coinfection_Mortality.description: Controls whether or not TB/HIV coinfection mortality is enabled.

Typhoid_Acute_Infectiousness.description: Daily shedding into contact and environmental reservoirs in colony-forming units

Typhoid_Chronic_Relative_Infectiousness.description: Relative infectiousness of chronic carriers to acute infections.

Typhoid_Prepatent_Relative_Infectiousnes.description: Relative infectiousness of prepatent infections to acute infections.

Typhoid_Protection_Per_Infection.description: Decrease in susceptibility per infection (exponential decrease).

Typhoid_Subclinical_Relative_Infectiousn.description: Relative infectiousness of subclinical infections to acute infections.

Typhoid_Carrier_Probability.description: The probability of becoming a chronic carrier after a subclinical or acute infection with gallstones.

Typhoid_6month_Susceptible_Fraction.description: Proportion of immune population at 6 months that moves to susceptible state.

Typhoid_3year_Susceptible_Fraction.description: Proportion of immune population at 3 years that moves to susceptible state.

Typhoid_Environmental_Exposure_Rate.description: Poisson rate determining daily number of exposures to the environmental transmission route.

Typhoid_Contact_Exposure_Rate.description: Poisson rate determining daily number of exposures to the contact transmission route.

Typhoid_6year_Susceptible_Fraction.description: Proportion of immune population of 6 year olds that moves to susceptible state.

Typhoid_Symptomatic_Fraction.description: Proportion of prepatent cases that become acute vs. subclinical.

Typhoid_Exposure_Lambda.description: The average number of typhoid exposures during time period.

Age_Dependent_Biting_Risk_Type.description: The type of functional form for age-dependent biting risk.

Newborn_Biting_Risk_Multiplier.description: Scale factor that defines the y-intercept of the linear portion of the biting risk curve when Age_Dependent_Biting_Risk_Type is set to LINEAR.

Use_Defaults.description: Set to true (1) if you don't want to have to specify all params for event coordinators and interventions. Use at own risk.

Base_Specificity.description: The specificity of the diagnostic. This sets the proportion of the time that individuals without the condition being tested receive a negative diagnostic test. When set to 1, the diagnostic always accurately reflects the lack of having the condition. When set to zero, then individuals who do not have the condition always receive a false-positive diagnostic test.

Base_Sensitivity.description: The sensitivity of the diagnostic. This sets the proportion of the time that individuals with the condition being tested receive a positive diagnostic test. When set to zero, then individuals who have the condition always receive a false-negative diagnostic test.

Enable_Is_Symptomatic.description: If true, requires an infection to be symptomatic to return a positive test.

Treatment_Fraction.description: The fraction of positive diagnoses that are treated.

Days_To_Diagnosis.description: The number of days from diagnosis (which is done when the intervention is distributed) until a positive response is performed.

Cost_To_Consumer.description: The unit 'cost' assigned to the diagnostic. Setting Cost_To_Consumer to zero for all other interventions, and to a non-zero amount for one intervention, provides a convenient way to track the number of times the intervention has been applied in a simulation.

Event_Or_Config.description: Specifies whether the current intervention (or a positive diagnosis, depending on the intervention class) distributes a nested intervention (the Config option) or an event will be broadcast which may trigger other interventions in the campaign file (the Event option).

Positive_Diagnosis_Event.description: If the test is positive, this specifies an event that can trigger another intervention when the event occurs. Only used if Event_Or_Config is set to Event.

Positive_Diagnosis_Config.description: The intervention distributed to individuals if they test positive. Only used when Event_Or_Config is set to Config.

Non_Adherence_Distribution.description: The non adherence probability value(s) assigned to the corresponding options in Non_Adherence_Options. The sum of non adherence distribution values must equal a total of 1.

Max_Dose_Consideration_Duration.description: The maximum number of days that an individual will consider taking the doses of the drug.

Took_Dose_Event.description: The event that triggers the drug intervention campaign.

Adherence_Config.description: A WaningEffect used to determine if the person is going to take the next dose.  WaningEffectMapCount can be used to set the probability for a particular dose.  WaningEffectMapLinearAge can be used to set the probability that a dose is take based on a person's age.  WaningEffectCombo can be used to combine them.

Doses.description: This is a two dimensional array of the drug names defined in the <config.Malaria_Drug_Params>.  Each inner array defines the drugs to be taken for a single 'dose'.  The number of doses is determined by the number of inner arrays.  An empty dose is allowed.

Dose_Interval.description: This is the number days to wait between the doses defined in the 'Doses' parameter.

If they are not being used, then this does not needed to be specified or can be empty string.  It cannot have a value if <config.Insecticides> does not define anything.

Drug_Type.description: Specifies the name of the drug treatment, such as DOTS or EmpiricTreatment, which can be useful for reporting from the simulation.

TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate.description: The daily rate at which treatment with an anti-TB drug causes inactivation in an individual with drug-sensitive TB.

TB_Drug_Cure_Rate.description: The daily probability of TB cure in an individual with drug-sensitive TB under drug treatment.

TB_Drug_Resistance_Rate.description: The daily probability that an individual with drug-sensitive TB will acquire MDR-TB under drug treatment. Only individuals who return to the latent state or fail can acquire MDR-TB.

TB_Drug_Relapse_Rate.description: The daily probability of TB inactivation and subsequent relapse in an individual with drug-sensitive TB under drug treatment.

Base_Specificity.description: The specificity of the diagnostic. This sets the proportion of the time that individuals without the condition being tested receive a negative diagnostic test. When set to 1, the diagnostic always accurately reflects the lack of having the condition. When set to zero, then individuals who do not have the condition always receive a false-positive diagnostic test.

Base_Sensitivity.description: The sensitivity of the diagnostic. This sets the proportion of the time that individuals with the condition being tested receive a positive diagnostic test. When set to zero, then individuals who have the condition always receive a false-negative diagnostic test.

Enable_Is_Symptomatic.description: If true, requires an infection to be symptomatic to return a positive test.

Treatment_Fraction.description: The fraction of positive diagnoses that are treated.

Days_To_Diagnosis.description: The number of days from diagnosis (which is done when the intervention is distributed) until a positive response is performed. The response to a negative diagnosis is done immediately when the diagnosis is made (at distribution of the intervention).

Event_Or_Config.description: Specifies whether the current intervention (or a positive diagnosis, depending on the intervention class) distributes a nested intervention (the Config option) or an event will be broadcast which may trigger other interventions in the campaign file (the Event option).

Positive_Diagnosis_Event.description: If the test is positive, this specifies an event that can trigger another intervention when the event occurs. Only used if Event_Or_Config is set to Event.

Positive_Diagnosis_Config.description: The intervention distributed to individuals if they test positive. Only used when Event_Or_Config is set to Config.

Negative_Diagnosis_Event.description: If 'Event_Or_Config' is set to 'Event', this parameter defines the event to be broadcasted on a negative test result.

Negative_Diagnosis_Config.description: If 'Event_Or_Config' is set to 'Config', this parameter defines a new intervention to be given to the person on a negative test result.

Defaulters_Event.description: Specifies an event that can trigger another intervention when the event occurs. Event_Or_Config must be set to 'Event', and an individual did not return for test results.

Defaulters_Config.description: The intervention configuration given out when an individual did not return for test results when Event_Or_Config is set to 'Config'.

Sample_Threshold.description: The threshold that delineates a positive versus negative sampling result. If the sample is greater than the threshold, a positive finding will result; if the value is less than the threshold, it will be negative. This does not include values equal to the threshold so that the threshold can be set to zero; if the threshold is zero, the test is simply looking for any deposit in the transmission pool.

When set to 1, the diagnostic always accurately reflects the lack of having the condition. When set to zero, then individuals who do not have the condition always receive a false-positive diagnostic test.

Base_Sensitivity.description: The likelihood that a positive measurement was made. If the contagion measurement is greater than the Sample_Threshold, a random number is drawn to determine if the detection was actually made.

Environment_IP_Key_Value.description: An IndividualProperty key:value pair that indicates a specific transmission pool, typically used to identify a location.  If none is provided, the sample will be taken on the entire node.

Negative_Diagnostic_Event.description: The event that will be broadcast to the node when the sample value is less than the threshold (e.g. the test is negative). If this is an empty string or set to NoTrigger, no event will be broadcast.

Positive_Diagnostic_Event.description: The event that will be broadcast to the node when the sample value is greater than the threshold (e.g. the test is positive). This cannot be an empty string or set to NoTrigger.

EIR_Type.description: Choose whether you want the EIR read in to be monthly or daily.

Monthly_EIR.description: An array of 12 elements that contain an entomological inoculation rate (EIR) for each month. Each value should be between 0 and 1000.

Daily_EIR.description: An array of 365 values where each value is the mean number of infectious bites experienced by an individual for that day of the year.

Scaling_Factor.description: A modifier that is multiplied by the EIR determined for the current day.

Intervention_Name.description: The optional name used to refer to this intervention as a means to differentiate it from others that use the same class.

Disqualifying_Properties.description: A list of NodeProperty key:value pairs that cause an intervention to be aborted. Generally used to control the flow of health care access. For example, to prevent the same individual from accessing health care via two different routes at the same time.

New_Property_Value.description: An optional NodeProperty key:value pair that will be assigned when the intervention is distributed. Generally used to indicate the broad category of health care cascade to which an intervention belongs to prevent individuals from accessing care through multiple pathways.

Relationship_Types.description: An array listing all possible relationship types for which partners can qualify for the intervention.

Minimum_Duration_Years.description: The minimum amount of time, in years, between relationship formation and the current time for the partner to qualify for the intervention.

Maximum_Partners.description: The maximum number of partners that will receive the intervention.

Prioritize_Partners_By.description: How to prioritize partners for the intervention, as long as they have been in a relationship longer than **Minimum_Duration_Years**.

Event_Or_Config.description: Specifies whether the current intervention (or a positive diagnosis, depending on the intervention class) distributes a nested intervention (the Config option) or an event will be broadcast which may trigger other interventions in the campaign file (the Event option).

Broadcast_Event.description: The event that is immediately broadcast to the partner. Required if **Event_or_Config** is set to Event.

Intervention_Config.description: The intervention definition that is immediately distributed to the partner. Required if **Event_Or_Config** is set to Config.

Treatment_Fraction_Negative_Diagnosis.description: The fraction of negative diagnoses that are treated.

Base_Specificity.description: The specificity of the diagnostic. This sets the proportion of the time that individuals without the condition being tested receive a negative diagnostic test. When set to 1, the diagnostic always accurately reflects the lack of having the condition. When set to zero, then individuals who do not have the condition always receive a false-positive diagnostic test.

Base_Sensitivity.description: The sensitivity of the diagnostic. This sets the proportion of the time that individuals with the condition being tested receive a positive diagnostic test. When set to zero, then individuals who have the condition always receive a false-negative diagnostic test.

Enable_Is_Symptomatic.description: If true, requires an infection to be symptomatic to return a positive test.

Treatment_Fraction.description: The fraction of positive diagnoses that are treated.

Days_To_Diagnosis.description: The number of days from diagnosis (which is done when the intervention is distributed) until a positive response is performed. The response to a negative diagnosis is done immediately when the diagnosis is made (at distribution of the intervention).

Cost_To_Consumer.description: The unit 'cost' assigned to the diagnostic. Setting Cost_To_Consumer to zero for all other interventions, and to a non-zero amount for one intervention, provides a convenient way to track the number of times the intervention has been applied in a simulation.

Event_Or_Config.description: Specifies whether the current intervention (or a positive diagnosis, depending on the intervention class) distributes a nested intervention (the Config option) or an event will be broadcast which may trigger other interventions in the campaign file (the Event option).

Positive_Diagnosis_Event.description: If the test is positive, this specifies an event that can trigger another intervention when the event occurs. Only used if Event_Or_Config is set to Event.

Positive_Diagnosis_Config.description: The intervention distributed to individuals if they test positive. Only used when Event_Or_Config is set to Config.

Negative_Diagnosis_Event.description: If 'Event_Or_Config' is set to 'Event', this parameter defines the event to be broadcasted on a negative test result.

Negative_Diagnosis_Config.description: If 'Event_Or_Config' is set to 'Config', this parameter defines a new intervention to be given to the person on a negative test result.

Defaulters_Event.description: Specifies an event that can trigger another intervention when the event occurs. Event_Or_Config must be set to 'Event', and an individual did not return for test results.

Defaulters_Config.description: The intervention configuration given out when an individual did not return for test results when Event_Or_Config is set to 'Config'.

Released_Number.description: The number of mosquitoes released in the intervention.

Released_Fraction.description: The fraction of the current poulation of mosquitoes to release.  The 'population' will depend on the gender of the mosquitos being released and it will be the population from the previous time step.

Released_Infectious.description: The fraction of vectors released that are to be infectious.  One can only use this feature when 'Malaria_Model'!='MALARIA_MECHANISTIC_MODEL_WITH_PARASITE_GENETICS'.

Released_Genome.description: This defines the alleles of the genome of the vectors to be released.  It must define all of the alleles including the gender 'gene'.  '*' is not allowed.

Base_Sensitivity.description: The sensitivity of the diagnostic. This sets the proportion of the time that individuals with the condition being tested receive a positive diagnostic test. When set to zero, then individuals who have the condition always receive a false-negative diagnostic test.

Enable_Is_Symptomatic.description: If true, requires an infection to be symptomatic to return a positive test.

Positive_Diagnosis_Event.description: If the test is positive, this specifies an event that can trigger another intervention when the event occurs. Only used if Event_Or_Config is set to Event.

Positive_Diagnosis_Config.description: The intervention distributed to individuals if they test positive. Only used when Event_Or_Config is set to Config.

Vaccine_Take.description: The rate at which delivered vaccines will successfully stimulate an immune response and achieve the desired efficacy.

Vaccine_Type.description: The type of vaccine to distribute in a vaccine intervention.

Efficacy_Is_Multiplicative.description: The overall vaccine efficacy when individuals receive more than one vaccine. When set to true (1), the vaccine efficacies are multiplied together; when set to false (0), the efficacies are additive.

Waning_Config.description: The configuration of Ivermectin killing efficacy and waning over time.

Intervention_Name.description: The optional name used to refer to this intervention as a means to differentiate it from others that use the same class.

Dont_Allow_Duplicates.description: If an individual's container has an intervention, set to true (1) to prevent them from receiving another copy of the intervention. Supported by all intervention classes.

Disqualifying_Properties.description: A list of IndividualProperty key:value pairs that cause an intervention to be aborted. Generally used to control the flow of health care access. For example, to prevent the same individual from accessing health care via two different routes at the same time.

New_Property_Value.description: An optional IndividualProperty key:value pair that will be assigned when the intervention is distributed. Generally used to indicate the broad category of health care cascade to which an intervention belongs to prevent individuals from accessing care through multiple pathways.

Base_Specificity.description: The specificity of the diagnostic. This sets the proportion of the time that individuals without the condition being tested receive a negative diagnostic test. When set to 1, the diagnostic always accurately reflects the lack of having the condition. When set to zero, then individuals who do not have the condition always receive a false-positive diagnostic test.

Base_Sensitivity.description: The sensitivity of the diagnostic. This sets the proportion of the time that individuals with the condition being tested receive a positive diagnostic test. When set to zero, then individuals who have the condition always receive a false-negative diagnostic test.

Enable_Is_Symptomatic.description: If true, requires an infection to be symptomatic to return a positive test.

Treatment_Fraction.description: The fraction of positive diagnoses that are treated.

Days_To_Diagnosis.description: The number of days from diagnosis (which is done when the intervention is distributed) until a positive response is performed.

Cost_To_Consumer.description: The unit 'cost' assigned to the diagnostic. Setting Cost_To_Consumer to zero for all other interventions, and to a non-zero amount for one intervention, provides a convenient way to track the number of times the intervention has been applied in a simulation.

Event_Or_Config.description: Specifies whether the current intervention (or a positive diagnosis, depending on the intervention class) distributes a nested intervention (the Config option) or an event will be broadcast which may trigger other interventions in the campaign file (the Event option).

Positive_Diagnosis_Event.description: If the test is positive, this specifies an event that can trigger another intervention when the event occurs. Only used if Event_Or_Config is set to Event.

Positive_Diagnosis_Config.description: The intervention distributed to individuals if they test positive. Only used when Event_Or_Config is set to Config.

The resulting waning effect value must be greater than 1.
